#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:10
msgid ""
"An axe is your tool of choice to cut down trees, wood-based blocks and other "
"blocks. Axes deal a lot of damage as well, but they are rather slow. Axes "
"can be used to strip bark and hyphae from trunks. They can also be used to "
"scrape blocks made of copper, reducing their oxidation stage or removing wax "
"from waxed variants."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:11
msgid ""
"To strip bark from trunks and hyphae, use the ax by right-clicking on them. "
"To reduce an oxidation stage from a block made of copper or remove wax from "
"waxed variants, right-click on them. Doors and trapdoors also require you to "
"hold down the sneak key while using the axe."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:28
msgid ""
"Pickaxes are mining tools to mine hard blocks, such as stone. A pickaxe can "
"also be used as weapon, but it is rather inefficient."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:40
msgid ""
"Shovels are tools for digging coarse blocks, such as dirt, sand and gravel. "
"They can also be used to turn grass blocks to grass paths. Shovels can be "
"used as weapons, but they are very weak."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:41
msgid ""
"To turn a grass block into a grass path, hold the shovel in your hand, then "
"use (rightclick) the top or side of a grass block. This only works when "
"there's air above the grass block."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:53
msgid ""
"Swords are great in melee combat, as they are fast, deal high damage and can "
"endure countless battles. Swords can also be used to cut down a few "
"particular blocks, such as cobwebs."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:70
msgid ""
"Shears are tools to shear sheep and to mine a few block types. Shears are a "
"special mining tool and can be used to obtain the original item from grass, "
"leaves and similar blocks that require cutting."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:71
msgid ""
"To shear sheep or carve faceless pumpkins, use the “place” key on them. "
"Faces can only be carved at the side of faceless pumpkins. Mining works as "
"usual, but the drops are different for a few blocks."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/init.lua:259
msgid "Shears"
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/mace.lua:6
msgid ""
"Solid Blocks of Steel. These are only forged if those that are brave enough "
"can defeat the trials that await them."
msgstr ""

#: mods/ITEMS/mcl_tools/mace.lua:7
msgid ""
"The mace is a slow melee weapon that deals incredible damage. “dig” key to "
"use it. This weapon has a cooldown of 1.6 seconds, but if you fall the mace "
"will deal more damage than if you are on the ground. The further you fall "
"the more damage done. If you hit a mob or player then you will receive no "
"fall damage, but beware. If you miss you will die. "
msgstr ""

